# `features/` (and sparse `components/tools`)

## `features/`

Use for **cross-surface domain slices**: the same substantive UI/logic must be composed from **more than one app surface**—typically **`app/(main)/.../page.tsx` plus the assistant **`GeneratedUILayout`** (`app/(main)/assistant/_generated-ui-layout.tsx`). Route-only consumers should prefer **`app/.../_name.tsx`** (see **generic-ui-components**).

- **One folder per slice** under **`features/<name>/`**: e.g. **`features/pantry/pantry-list.tsx`** + **`pantry-list.actions.ts`** (same pattern as [bulletproof-react `src/features`](https://github.com/alan2207/bulletproof-react/tree/master/apps/nextjs-app/src/features)).
- **`.actions.ts`**: **`"use server"`** module colocated next to its client counterpart; exported names stay feature-specific (**`searchPantryCatalogAction`**, etc.).
- **Imports**: **`app`** surfaces (pages and route-colocated **`_*.tsx`** partials such as **`_generated-ui-layout.tsx`**) compose **`@/features/...`**; keep substantive domain UI in **`features/`**, not ad hoc under **`app/`** except as thin wrappers.

## `components/tools`

**`components/tools`:** reserve for assistant-adjacent UI that stays **outside** **`app/`** (rare once route colocation covers preview shells).

**Assistant preview shell** lives beside the route as **`app/(main)/assistant/_generated-ui-layout.tsx`**; it composes **`features/`** slices—not primary **`/routes`** domain markup that ships without the assistant surface.
